# Builder.io Fusion — Project Rules

Non-negotiable rules for every task. Full detail in `AGENTS.md` and `docs/skills/`.

## Dev Server
- Always start with `npm run dev -- --webpack`
- Never use `next dev` without `--webpack` — Turbopack is incompatible with Builder Dev Tools

## Config & Model Names
- Never hardcode Builder model names — always use `config.models.*` from `config.ts`
- API key is `config.envs.builderApiKey` — never inline it
- When adding a new model, add its name to `config.ts` before using it anywhere

## Builder SDK
- Never use `<Content>` directly — always `import { RenderBuilderContent } from "@/components/builder/RenderBuilderContent"`
- Always guard notFound: `if (!content && !isEditing() && !isPreviewing()) return notFound()`
- Always guard `subscribeToEditor` with a `builder.preview` URL param check — see `docs/skills/builder-io.md`
- Never use `dangerouslySetInnerHTML` on Builder HTML fields without DOMPurify sanitization

## Imports & Paths
- Always use the `@/` path alias — never relative paths like `../../`
- Import shadcn components from their own file: `import { Button } from "@/components/ui/button"` — no barrel
- Import Text from `@/components/ui/text`; FormInput from `@/components/ui/form-input`

## Component File Structure
- shadcn primitives → flat file in `components/ui/my-component.tsx`
- All other components → four-file folder in `components/MyComponent/` (see `component-structure.mdc` and `components/HeroSplit/`)
